      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T16:41:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Done.\n\u003e \n\u003e (On the observation and discussion...)\n\u003e \n\u003e I agree, the plan you gave would be best possible. I\u0027d suggest a full-width-pid, if 4 redundant bytes isn\u0027t too big a price to pay... it feels like an unnecessary optimization.\n\nIt’s not that the bytes are precious and I’m trying to optimize them away, it’s just that I like to avoid ambiguities and redundancies. If the low bits duplicate each other in two locations, it’s an extra thing to get out of sync, and an extra thing that a reader would ideally remember to check for equivalence. Another design that avoids redundancy throws readers that don’t understand the Crashpad extension under the bus by writing a constant value to the legacy field, putting all of the real bits in the extension field.\n\nCertainly not critical.",
      "parentUuid": "1068132f_da82fb4d",
